rent furnace is over 15 years old, it may be working harder than it should. New models boast advanced features like variable-speed blowers and smart thermostat compatibility, giving you better control over your indoor climate. Plus, with modern energy-efficient models, you can reduce heating costs while keeping your home toasty all winter.<\/p>\n\n\n\n<h2>Heat Pumps: A Year-Round Love Story<\/h2>\n\n\n\n<p>If you\u2019re looking for a system that does it all, consider a heat pump. These units provide both heating and cooling, making them a great choice for homeowners who want energy efficiency year-round. Heat pumps work by transferring heat rather than generating it, making them an eco-friendly option with lower operating costs. Whether you\u2019re heating up for winter or cooling down for summer, a heat pump keeps your home comfortable without breaking the bank.<\/p>\n\n\n\n<h2>Boilers: The Quiet and Reliable Partner<\/h2>\n\n\n\n<p>Boilers might not get as much attention as furnaces, but they provide consistent and even heat without the need for ducts. If you love the idea of radiant floor heating or prefer a system that doesn\u2019t blow air around, a boiler upgrade could be the perfect match for your home. Newer models are highly efficient, and with proper maintenance, they can last for decades.<\/p>\n\n\n\n<h2>Ductless Mini-Splits: The Flexible Option<\/h2>\n\n\n\n<p>If your home has areas that never seem to warm up properly, a ductless mini-split system could be the answer. These systems allow you to heat specific zones without relying on ductwork, giving you complete control over different rooms. They\u2019re also incredibly efficient, making them an excellent choice for supplementing your current heating system or providing an alternative for homes without traditional ductwork.<\/p>\n\n\n\n<h2>Why Upgrade Now?<\/h2>\n\n\n\n<p>February might not seem like the obvious time for an HVAC upgrade, but it makes perfect sense. Winter weather reminds us just how important a reliable heating system is, and HVAC companies often have better availability outside of peak seasons. Plus, with energy rebates and financing options available, investing in a more efficient system now could mean major savings in the long run.<\/p>\n\n\n\n<h2>Show Your Home Some Love<\/h2>\n\n\n\n<p>Upgrading your heating system isn\u2019t just about staying warm\u2014it\u2019s about improving your home\u2019s efficiency, lowering energy bills, and ensuring your family\u2019s comfort for years to come. So, if you\u2019re ready to make the switch, now\u2019s the time to explore your options.<\/p>\n\n\n\n<p class=\"has-text-align-center\"><strong><a href=\"https:\/\/www.weathermakerscomfort.com\/contact\/message\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"noreferrer noopener\">Contact WeatherMakers Heating, Cooling &amp; Plumbing.<\/a>\u00a0<em>Ensuring Your Comfort\u2026 For Life!<\/em><\/strong><\/p>\n","protected":false},"excerpt":{"rendered":"<p> A heating upgrade in Edmonton isn\u2019t just about warmth; it\u2019s an investment in efficiency, reliability, and long-term savings. Let\u2019s explore different heating systems and why upgrading now can be a smart (and heartfelt) decision.<\/p>\n","protected":false},"author":1,"featured_media":0,"comment_status":"closed","ping_status":"closed","sticky":false,"template":"","format":"standard","meta":[],"categories":[160],"tags":[139,161],"_links":{"self":[{"href":"https:\/\/www.weathermakerscomfort.com\/blog\/wp-json\/wp\/v2\/posts\/2972"}],"collection":[{"href":"https:\/\/www.weathermakerscomfort.com\/blog\/wp-json\/wp\/v2\/posts"}],"about":[{"href":"https:\/\/www.weathermakerscomfort.com\/blog\/wp-json\/wp\/v2\/types\/post"}],"author":[{"embeddable":true,"href":"https:\/\/www.weathermakerscomfort.com\/blog\/wp-json\/wp\/v2\/users\/1"}],"replies":[{"embeddable":true,"href":"https:\/\/www.weathermakerscomfort.com\/blog\/wp-json\/wp\/v2\/comments?post=2972"}],"version-history":[{"count":8,"href":"https:\/\/www.weathermakerscomfo